   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The long lifetime of Reality systems is possible due to proper
maintenance, service and when needed spare part replacement. Depending
on the system application and environment, it might be necessary to
store parts for a period of time. Before storing a part it is important
to consider the shelf life, storage condition and type of packing
so the part can fulfil its design life.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">In this document the
Reality definition of shelf life and design life are defined. For applicable
parts the shelf life, storage condition and packing specifications
are specified.</p>
